<html xmlns:o="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office"
      xmlns:w="urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:word"
      xmlns="http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Inveringo Event Description</title>
</head>
<body style="font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;">
    <h1 style="text-align: center;">INVERINGO - EVENT DESCRIPTION</h1>
    <br>
    <h2>Round 1 – The Matrix Mission &amp; Strategic Selection</h2>
    <p>Teams will face a 9-cell computational grid containing 4 Moderate and 5 Hard technical questions.</p>
    <p><b>Game Setup:</b> Players first strategize by dragging and dropping to arrange the sequence of the 9 grid cells before the game starts.</p>
    <p><b>Time Limit:</b> 10 minutes.</p>
    
    <h3>Task 1: Question Selection &amp; Risk Assessment</h3>
    <p>Before attempting each question, teams must lock in a risk strategy. They must manually type the correct answer to the prompt.</p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Safe Mode:</b> Standard play with zero risk.</li>
        <li><b>Risk Mode:</b> High-stakes play for greater rewards but steep penalties for mistakes.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Scoring Rules – Round 1</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Safe Mode:</b> Correct Answer = <b>+10 points</b> | Wrong Answer = <b>0 points</b> (No penalty)</li>
        <li><b>Risk Mode:</b> Correct Answer = <b>+25 points</b> | Wrong Answer = <b>−15 points</b></li>
        <li><b>Streak Bonus:</b> Three consecutive correct answers (in either mode) grants a <b>+15 points</b> bonus.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Special Advantages</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><b>The Power Cell:</b> One random cell in the 9-cell grid acts as a hidden "Power Cell." If a team answers the Power Cell correctly, they receive a special reward module where they choose ONE of the following:
            <ol>
                <li>Add a <b>+20 point</b> flat bonus to their score.</li>
                <li>Nullify their last <b>-15 point</b> Risk Mode penalty.</li>
                <li>Claim a <b>Free Risk Token</b> (makes their next failed Risk Mode attempt penalty-free).</li>
            </ol>
        </li>
        <li><b>The Riddle Key:</b> At the 3, 6, and 9 correct answer milestones, fragments of a final target word are unlocked. Successfully completing the grid gives teams the full password required to boot up Round 2.</li>
    </ul>
    
    <hr>

    <h2>Round 2 – The Protocol Challenge (Reverse Engineering)</h2>
    <p>Teams will enter their secret word from Round 1 as an <b>Access Key</b>. They will be presented with a customized protocol of 5 advanced, Staff-Engineer difficulty questions.</p>
    <p><b>Time Limit:</b> 20 minutes</p>

    <h3>Task 2: Reverse Code Tracing (Dual-Input Validation)</h3>
    <p>Instead of finding the output, teams are given a complex code snippet and its <b>Expected Final Output</b>. The team must reverse-engineer the logic and provide <b>TWO entirely distinct valid inputs</b> (Input A and Input B) that would both successfully generate that exact output.</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Teams are allowed a <b>maximum of 2 attempts</b> per question.</li>
        <li>If a team fails both attempts, they are locked out of the question and forced to move on.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Scoring Rules – Round 2</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Correct Dual-Input:</b> <b>+50 points</b></li>
        <li><b>Incorrect Guess:</b> <b>−10 points</b> per failed attempt.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Special Advantage: The Hint System</h3>
    <p>Teams are provided with <b>2 Hint Cards</b> for the entirety of Round 2 (maximum 1 hint allowed per question). Teams can choose what level of help they need at the cost of their score:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><b>Soft Hint</b> (General logical direction): Cost <b>−5 points</b></li>
        <li><b>Strong Hint</b> (Directly points out edge cases and trick lines): Cost <b>−10 points</b></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Judging Criteria &amp; Tie-Breakers</h2>
    <p>The final winners are determined by their <b>total accumulated score</b> across both rounds.<br>
    If two or more teams tie with the exact same final score, the system will evaluate the following tie-breaker metrics (in order of priority) based on Round 2 performance:</p>
    <ol>
        <li><b>Time Efficiency:</b> The team with the shortest total time taken.</li>
        <li><b>Resource Management:</b> The team that used the least number of Hint Cards.</li>
        <li><b>Accuracy:</b> The team with the least number of total incorrect attempts.</li>
    </ol>
    <p>The team that excels in these technical metrics will be declared the Winner.</p>
</body>
</html>
